.TH fmt_long 3
.SH NAME
fmt_int \- write an ASCII representation of an integer
.SH SYNTAX
.B #include <fmt.h>

unsigned int \fBfmt_int\fP(char *\fIdest\fR,int \fIsource\fR);

.SH DESCRIPTION
fmt_int writes an ASCII representation ('-' and '0' to '9', base 10) of
\fIsource\fR to \fIdest\fR and returns the number of bytes written.

fmt_int does not append \\0.

If \fIdest\fR equals FMT_LEN (i.e. is zero), fmt_long returns the number
of bytes it would have written.

For convenience, fmt.h defines the integer FMT_LONG to be big enough to
contain every possible fmt_int output plus \\0.
